block content
    section.container
        h1 Hello #{user.name}!
        p This website contains the documentation for the node.js based stack of technologies and patterns I have used for applications I am involved with where able.
        p The code running this site is itself part of the documentation intended to be a small idealistic example of the approaches I have taken, so it is easy for someone to familiarise themselves with any of the tools I have built for UQ.
        p So make sure to ask James Baker (me) for access to a copy of the codebase for this program if you are trying to understand how I structure my applications.
        blockquote.fs08 
            span.bold important note:
            span.pleft025 not every system has been able to use everything in this stack, for example grade is a system that was built with jquery, and the version of datatables that relies on jquery instead due to legacy.

